<p>&#8216;A legal case involving a group of rugby players diagnosed with early-onset dementia and other irreversible neurological impairments now looks destined for the courts. Proceedings are to be issued by Rylands Law on behalf of a group of professional and semi-professional players against World Rugby, the Rugby Football Union and the Welsh Rugby Union.&#8217;</p>
<p><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2022/jul/25/case-against-rugby-union-governing-bodies-on-dementia-destined-for-courts">Full Story</a></p><p>The Guardian, 25th July 2022</p><p>Source: <a href="https://www.theguardian.com">www.theguardian.com</a></p>